A special URL, '/jscoverage-clear-local-storage.html', has been added to clear JSCover's local
storage. Alternatively, the following JavaScript can be executed:
localStorage.removeItem('jscover');

                    Example of JavaScript to store the report and wait for the store process to complete:
                    ((JavascriptExecutor) webClient).executeScript("window.jscoverFinished = false;");
((JavascriptExecutor) webClient).executeScript("jscoverage_report('', function(){window.jscoverFinished=true;});");
    (new WebDriverWait(webClient, 10000))
        .until(new ExpectedCondition<Boolean>() {
            public Boolean apply(WebDriver d) {
                return (Boolean)((JavascriptExecutor) webClient).executeScript("return window.jscoverFinished;");
            }});
                    The same with Java8 lamba:
                    ((JavascriptExecutor) webClient).executeScript("window.jscoverFinished = false;");
((JavascriptExecutor) webClient).executeScript("jscoverage_report('', function(){window.jscoverFinished=true;});");
    (new WebDriverWait(webClient, 10000))
        .until((ExpectedCondition<Boolean>) d -> (Boolean)((JavascriptExecutor) webClient).executeScript("return window.jscoverFinished;"));

